 &quot;Something isnt right.&quot; She said softly. She nuged Marpe to wake up and looked down at Mel. &quot;Mel, now listen to me. I know you want to be there with us to recuse Hippolyte, but this is not a place for you at this moment. So I want you to stay here, get things ready for her when we bring her back. I am sure that she will need your help.&quot; She knew that Mel would get hurt fighting against these Romans and would not  have that at this moment. She was the next in line responsible for Hipployte's family. <br>
 &quot;Gather what weapons we have and those of us that have horses, mount up.&quot; Solari said in a commanding, but gentle tone. &quot;Its time.&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#993300>(4/26/03 10:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=179>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> Marpe quickly rose from her nap, after Solari awoke her.  And then listened to the Queen as she gave orders.  Looking to Melanippe, she knew it would be hard for the young girl to stay back.  &quot;Mel, guard the two women...Cassandra and her sister.  They do not know how to protect themselves.&quot;  She didn't mean to step in, but thought that might help the young warrior stay back from the battle.<br>
<br>
Then with Solari's orders, the guard quickly took off to her horse and got up on the saddle.  Pulling her reigns back as the horse instantly had the urge to race.  Marpe awaited the Queen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elektraamazon>Elektra Amazon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#993300>(4/26/03 10:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=180>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> Before the Queen could even finish her words, Elektra was mounted and ready.  The blood on her neck had finally stopped bleeding.  But, still the assassin felt that Hippolyte was not out of danger still.  She was thankful to finally hear the words from Solari that they were going to ride to fight against the men. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 884<br> <font color=#993300>(4/26/03 10:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=181>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> The wolves seemed to run off back into the forest.  Calming the nerves of most of the men of the village.  Marxus grumbled tho.  As he threw Hippolyte back into the hut.  Falling to the floor, Hipp pushed herself up and then stood slowely. Grabbing her arms, he slammed her back into the pole and tied her.  &quot;I guess I need to get you fed.  Your no good to me starved.&quot;  <br>
<br>
He turned and stepped to the door of the hut, motioning for guards to come and watch Hippolyte.  And then he dissappeared.<br>
<br>
Hipp was now truly weak.  She couldn't hold her head up, for the loss of blood and strength.  It had been many days since she had eaten back in camp.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiares>Alexiares</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#993300>(4/26/03 10:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=182>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> The door of the hut slowely opened, and in walked a young woman dressed in a very simple greek peasant clothing.  In her hands she held a small bowl carefully.  Her eyes were cast down to the ground as she walked up to the woman tied to the post.  Then lifting her eyes, she thought she would drop the bowl.<br>
<br>
Alexiares did not know who this woman was, but it was clear to her that the woman was an amazon of importance.  Even more so, the woman wore a golden belt that signified she was a Queen.  <br>
<br>
Glancing to the guards, she didn't dare speak or tell the amazon who she was.  Alexiares had kept it quiet over the year she had spent as a captured slave.  Picking up a bit of the bread that soaked in beef broth in the bowl, she tenderly lifted it up to the amazons lips.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#993300>(4/27/03 2:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=183>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> Odessa looked to the Wolf, blinked,a nd then ran to Solari<br>
